Description. Male ( Holotype , Heredia Province, Costa Rica , MCTP 33749 ). Total length 21.94 . Carapace 10.64 long, 10.37 wide, light brown with a median irregular light brown band; laterals dark brown with short dark brown bristles; fovea marked (
Fig. 3
). Clypeus dark brown, 1.24 high. Anterior eye row recurved, 2.01 wide; posterior recurved 3.65 wide. Eye diameters: AME 0.46 , ALE 0.31 , PME 0.83 , PLE 0.77 ; interdistances: AME-AME 0.31 , AME-ALE 0.12 , PME-PME 0.43 , PME-PLE 0.74 ; median ocular quadrangle: OQA 1.17 , OQP 1.79 , OQH 1.67 . Chelicerae dark brown, frontal face bristly; promargin and retromargin of fang furrow with three teeth equidistant and equal in size. Sternum yellow, light brown laterally, bristly; 5.58 long, 5.05 wide. Labium dark brown, 1.86 long, 1.99 wide. Legs light brown with a dark brown irregular patches, relative length: IV–II–I–III, I—femur 17.82 / tibia-patella 19.15 / metatarsus 19.55 / tarsus 12.10 / total 68.62 ; II— 20.08 / 20.74 / 21.81 / 12.90 / 75.53 ; III— 16.35 / 19.10 / 16.22 / 10.64 / 62.31 ; IV— 21.14 / 26.06 / 25.93 / 15.29 / 88.42 . Ventral pairs of macrosetae on tibiae:
