Superior tarsal claw with seven teeth (
Fig. 14
). Abdomen, 10.90 long, dorsum dark gray, bristly and with three pairs of sigillae (
Fig. 3
). Venter light brown, scattered bristles. Ventral division of the median apophysis (VD) of the male palpus with an acute apex ( Figs 6, 7 ). Dorsal division of the median apophysis (DD) with a distal tooth-like projection ( Figs 7 , 10 ) and short guide (G) ( Figs 7 , 10 ). Retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA) prominent (
Fig. 8
). Ental division of RTA ( END ) short and retrolaterally curved (
Fig. 11
). Ectal division (ECD) of RTA with a lamellar projection, dorsally grooved ( Figs 12, 13 ).

Female ( Paratype , same locality as holotype , MCTP 33750 ). Total length 25.27 . Carapace 10.37 long, 10.39 wide, colour as in male (
Fig. 4
